The web consists of 3 programming languages:
-HTML
-CSS
-JavaScript

HTML, HyperText Markup Language
-HTML is everywhere, used in websites, apps and various software where web technology is involved.
-It serves for content like words, images, videos, audios, forms and interactive experiences.
-HTML grants access to a wide range of built in browser functionalities

CSS, Cascading Style Sheets, is like the stylist of the web page. It is responsible for how everything looks-the colours, fonts and sizes.It is also capable 
of adding cool animations and interactions to spice things up.

JavaScript is a programming language that allows you to create cool and interactive stuff.
-JavaScript is behind the scenes making things work smoothly for the users. If there is a issue with the code or the browser is outdated and does not understand the
code, it throws in the towel. It refuses to run that JavaScript and will not even try to figure out what to do. That is why JavaScript can be a bit fragile at times.
