HTML Headlines
Marking up headlines come is six different types h1-h6 (h1 being the largest font)

The opening and closing tags: Paragraph <p> </p>

There are four elements related to BOLD and ITALIC (x2 elements each) "<i>" and "<em>" element to add emphasis "<strong>" element, which is used to show importance,
seriousness, or urgency "<b>" element is more generic and neutral.
make certain words bold without conveying any meaning, we can use the "<b>" element
Each item in the list is enclosed in an <li> element, which represents a list item
To define the entire list and specify its type, we wrap all the items in a <ul> element, which stands for an unordered list.
use <ol>. The term "ol" stands for ordered list
a <dt> tag, which stands for definition term
a <dd> tag, which stands for definition description
a <dl> tag, representing the definition list
These two elements, < cite > and ,< blockquote > serve a semantic purpose.
The important thing is that elements should be nested within each other in a way that makes sense.
<time datetime="2025-05-08">May 8, 2025</time>.
HTML simplifies this by using a single element called <time>
(<time>) and a closing tag (</time>). For example, we can use it like this: <time>May 8th</time> or <time>May 8th 2025</time>
we need to type "&lt;"H4 headline instead of displaying "H4"
The br element is a simple tag without an opening or closing tag.
